{"actor":"Christopher Bartling","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-02T10:41:48Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":43,"issue_id":"otherworlds-rpg-ta6","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"otherworlds-rpg-ta6\",\"title\":\"Replace Uuid::new_v4() with DeterministicRng for event IDs\",\"description\":\"All 7 domain crates use Uuid::new_v4() for event_id in domain methods, breaking the replay determinism manifesto constraint. Fix requires: (1) Extend DeterministicRng trait with a next_uuid() method, (2) Thread \\u0026mut dyn DeterministicRng through all domain methods alongside Clock, (3) Update all aggregate domain methods to use rng.next_uuid() instead of Uuid::new_v4(), (4) Update all command handler signatures to pass rng, (5) Update all tests to use SequenceRng or equivalent. Affects: narrative, character, rules, world-state, inventory, session, content aggregates.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"chris.bartling@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T16:37:44Z\",\"created_by\":\"Christopher Bartling\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T16:37:44Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Christopher Bartling","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-02T11:47:55Z","event_type":"closed","id":44,"issue_id":"otherworlds-rpg-ta6","new_value":"All 7 bounded contexts updated: Uuid::new_v4() replaced with rng.next_uuid() in domain methods, command handlers, and API routes. 352 tests pass, clippy clean.","old_value":""}
{"actor":"Christopher Bartling","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-02T11:55:32Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":45,"issue_id":"otherworlds-rpg-mqe","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"otherworlds-rpg-mqe\",\"title\":\"Add PostgreSQL integration tests for domain crates\",\"description\":\"All domain crate tests use RecordingEventRepository (mock). No crate tests the full round-trip through PgEventRepository with a real database. Add integration tests in otherworlds-api/tests/ that exercise each bounded context's command and query handlers against PostgreSQL, verifying event persistence, reconstitution, and optimistic concurrency. The existing 4 integration tests (character_test.rs) provide a pattern to follow.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"chris.bartling@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T16:37:52Z\",\"created_by\":\"Christopher Bartling\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T16:37:52Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Christopher Bartling","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-02T12:17:46Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":46,"issue_id":"otherworlds-rpg-mqe","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"otherworlds-rpg-mqe\",\"title\":\"Add PostgreSQL integration tests for domain crates\",\"description\":\"All domain crate tests use RecordingEventRepository (mock). No crate tests the full round-trip through PgEventRepository with a real database. Add integration tests in otherworlds-api/tests/ that exercise each bounded context's command and query handlers against PostgreSQL, verifying event persistence, reconstitution, and optimistic concurrency. The existing 4 integration tests (character_test.rs) provide a pattern to follow.\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"chris.bartling@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T16:37:52Z\",\"created_by\":\"Christopher Bartling\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T17:55:33Z\"}"}
